It's just so much more work.

70
00:04:23,023 --> 00:04:24,857
I was just giving her a hard time.

71
00:04:24,925 --> 00:04:28,061
Can I interest you in the same?

72
00:04:28,128 --> 00:04:30,563
And I'm supposed to tell you in person

73
00:04:30,631 --> 00:04:31,931
that Mr. Pryce will be taking off

74
00:04:31,999 --> 00:04:33,933
the last two weeks
of August for his son's visit.

75
00:04:34,001 --> 00:04:36,002
You had to tell me that in person?

76
00:04:36,070 --> 00:04:39,339
- So depressing.
- He doesn't want a memo circulating.

77
00:04:39,406 --> 00:04:41,240
He's afraid people will stop working.

78
00:04:41,308 --> 00:04:43,543
What are you doing in August?

79
00:04:43,610 --> 00:04:45,478
I'm not sure.

80
00:04:45,546 --> 00:04:48,448
Well, what are you doing this afternoon?

81
00:04:48,515 --> 00:04:51,351
The same thing I do
every afternoon... Working...

82
00:04:51,418 --> 00:04:53,820
Which is what I'm trying to do right now.

83
00:04:53,887 --> 00:04:55,388
It's not cute.

84
00:04:56,924 --> 00:04:58,591
Joanie.

85
00:04:58,659 --> 00:05:00,560
Jesus. I'm sorry.

86
00:05:00,627 --> 00:05:02,995
What did you say to her?

87
00:05:03,063 --> 00:05:04,397
What does that have to do with you?

88
00:05:06,066 --> 00:05:08,101
Her husband got called up.

89
00:05:08,168 --> 00:05:10,136
He's going to Vietnam right after basic.

90
00:05:10,204 --> 00:05:12,171
Vietnam.

91
00:05:12,239 --> 00:05:14,407
That's not good.

92
00:05:14,475 --> 00:05:17,110
It's okay. We've all been
walking on eggshells.

93
00:05:23,183 --> 00:05:24,784
Good afternoon, all.

94
00:05:24,852 --> 00:05:26,786
I know you don't like to be bombarded

95
00:05:26,854 --> 00:05:28,354
the moment you walk in,
but Fillmore and Secor

96
